sub_title: Poland Partner Account Manager at NetApp
summary:
Hi there,

First of all, thanks for dropping by.

About me (personally):
I am a traveler and a story teller, constantly looking for new exciting places to visit and knowledge to absorb. And thanks to visiting more than 30 different countries (so far ;)), I am able to build relationships with people representing different mentalities and backgrounds, but most importantly, understand them better, their needs and challenges they face, approach them individually yet, on a global scale.

About me (professionally): 
The mission I undertook at NetApp is to help our ( both potential and existing) customers, identifying their challenges and goals, offer possible solutions NetApp can provide using the data fabric and connecting them to NetApp specialists and our amazing partner ecosystem for optimal results. 

Also, being a follower and an admirer of Carl Gustav Jung work, Brian Tracy (motivation&growth), Connor Neill (public speaking), Gabor Mate, Wendy Suzuki, and many more, infused me with knowledge and skills not only improving the professional aspects of my life, but also personal ones, slowly shaping my desired future.
